- "star players" refer to players who are ranked 1st in their positions based on average yards per game;
- "shining stars in their positions" refers to the best performers in quarterback, running back, and wide receiver roles;
- "high average performance" is defined as teams with a total average yards per game greater than 1000.

- "prominent quarterback" refers to the quarterback with the highest total yards gained;
- "total yards gained" is the sum of yards gained from all pass attempts;
- "active" means the player is currently playing in the league.

- "Star players" refers to the top 5 players in each position;
- "Shone the brightest" refers to having the highest total yards;
- "Combined light of their passing, rushing, and receiving yards" refers to the sum of yards gained in passing, rushing, and receiving statistics;
- "Brilliance of their total yards" refers to the total yards in descending order.

- "Active player" refers to a player whose `active` column is set to 1;
- "Running back" is a position in football known for their speed and agility in rushing the ball;
- "Rushing yards" are the total yards gained by a player when running with the ball;
- "Rushing attempts" are the number of times a player tries to advance the ball by running;
- "Touchdowns" are the number of times a player scores by carrying the ball into the end zone.

- "Last season" refers to the year 2023;
- "Top 10 players" are determined by their total passing yards;
- "Top 5 teams" are determined by the number of games they won where their score was higher than the opponent's score;
- "Top 3 conferences" are determined by the average attendance at games involving teams in those conferences.

- "Seasoned players" refers to players who have played in more than one game;
- "Consistent performance" refers to the average yards gained per game;
- "Average rushing yards per game" is calculated by dividing the total yards gained by the number of games played.

- "versatile player" refers to a player who excels in both rushing and receiving;
- "total yards" is the sum of rushing and receiving yards;
- "physical attributes" include height and weight.

- 'Top three players' refers to the players ranked 1, 2, and 3 within their teams based on total yards gained;
- 'Outperformed the average' means their total yards are greater than the average total yards across all players and games;
- 'Total yards gained' includes passing, rushing, and receiving yards.

- "shining stars" refers to the top players in each team;
- "precise aim" refers to the highest number of completions;
- "longest reach" refers to the highest total yards;
- "most decisive strikes" refers to the highest number of touchdowns.

- "Running back" is a position in football where the player is primarily responsible for running with the ball;
- "Rushing yards" refers to the total distance a player gains by running with the ball during a game;
- "Average rushing yards" is calculated by dividing the total rushing yards by the number of rushing attempts.

- "reigns supreme" refers to being the best or top in a particular category;
- "realm of victories" refers to the context of winning games;
- "teams" are part of a "conference" in sports leagues;
- "average number of wins" is calculated by summing the wins of all teams in a conference and dividing by the number of teams.
